🧑‍💼 Employee Management Portal

A full-stack Employee Management System built using Java, Spring Boot, JPA, MySQL, Thymeleaf, and
JavaScript to streamline HR operations like employee management, payroll, attendance, and request handling.
👇

🎯 Problem Statement
The manual management of employee data or the utilization of disparate systems frequently results in the following issues:
- Scattered employee records across multiple files/sheets
- No centralized system to track attendance, payroll, and requests
- Delays in processing employee requests (leave, updates, etc.)
- Lack of real-time insights into department-wise employee distribution
- Difficulty in filtering/searching employee data efficiently
- Manual payroll generation, which is time-consuming and error-prone

💡 Solution Approach
This project was built to provide a centralized and automated employee management system that:
- Maintains all employee data within a structured database.
- Provides role-based dashboards for both Administrators and Users.
- Automates payroll slip generation and attendance tracking.
- Enables real-time dashboard updates, facilitating better decision-making.
- Simplifies employee management through filtering and search functionalities.
- Streamlines communication via a request handling system.

🧠 Design Thinking (What I kept in mind)
While building this project, the focus was on:
🔹 Real-world usability
Designed features similar to actual HR systems used in companies
🔹 Separation of roles
Clear distinction between Admin and User functionalities
🔹 Scalability & Clean Architecture
Used layered structure:
 Controller → Service → Repository
🔹 Dynamic Data Handling
Dashboard updates automatically when data changes (no manual refresh logic)
🔹 Efficiency & Performance
Implemented filtering (by name, salary, department) to handle large datasets
🔹 Automation over manual work
Payroll and attendance handled programmatically instead of manually
🔹 User Experience (UX)
Simple UI using Thymeleaf so users can easily navigate and perform actions

🚀 Outcome
Reduced manual effort in managing employee records
Improved data organization and accessibility
Enabled faster decision-making using real-time insights
Created a scalable base for future HR system enhancements

🚀 Features 
 This project is two role based Admin and User Dashboad
📊 Admin Dashboard
*  Dynamic Dashboard: Real-time updates upon employee additions, department-wise employee counts, and request status tracking (Pending / Approved / Rejected)
*  Employee Management: Facilitates the addition, update, and deletion of employees, along with the ability to view a comprehensive employee list.
*  Filtering & Search: Enables filtering of employees by Name, Department, and Salary.
*  Print Functionality: Provides the capability to easily print employee records.
*  Payroll Management: Allows for the generation of salary/payroll slips, with download and print functionalities.
*  Attendance Reports: Enables the tracking and viewing of employee attendance.

👨‍🔧 User Dashboard
User Dashboard Features:
*   View personal profile
*   Check attendance records
*   Download salary slips
*   Send requests to admin
*   Track request status

## Tech Stack

**Backend:**
*   Java
*   Spring Boot
*   Spring Data JPA
*   Spring Security
*   REST APIs

**Frontend:**
*   Thymeleaf
*   HTML
*   CSS
*   JavaScript

**Database:**
*   MySQL

